-- slice 4: pass a lambda to a higher-order function that calls it INDIRECTLY.
-- `applyTo`'s body `f x` has a head (`f`) that is a parameter, not a known
-- top-level function — so it lowers to an indirect call (load code_ptr from the
-- closure cell, pass the closure word as the leading argument).
applyTo f x = f x
main = applyTo (y => y * 2) 21
